About PySul 2025

Python Sul (PySul) 2025 is an event that brings together Python enthusiasts and professionals to explore its various applications, including web development, data science, artificial intelligence, automation, and DevOps, with the goal of promoting learning, networking, and the exchange of experiences.

Talks

Talks on Python, AI, web, and more.

Workshops

Join hands-on sessions to enhance your skills.

Networking and Connections

Connect with other Python professionals and enthusiasts.

Python Community

Be part of a welcoming and diverse environment.

Call for Proposals

Want to share knowledge with the community?
Be a speaker and be part of it!

How to Participate?

  • Technical talks about Python and its ecosystem.
  • Python in different areas: web, data science, AI, IoT
  • Success stories and practical experiences
  • Topics on career and professional development
  • Diversity and inclusion initiatives in technology

Available Formats

Talk (40min)

Technical or inspirational presentations for the general audience.

Workshop (180min)

Hands-on sessions with interactive activities.

Lightning Talk* (5min)

Quick and dynamic presentations on any topic.
*Submissions during the event

Instagram Telegram Whatsapp

Python Sul (or PySul) is a community-driven event that brings together people passionate about Python and technology.
Since 2017, it has been touring the states in the southern region of Brazil with annual traveling editions, fostering knowledge exchange and community strengthening.

Local: Porto Alegre - RS
